Added patch.  Richard, this should be a safe fix.  Please look
at the code and ensure I crossed all the t's, and dotted the i's.
This problem still exists in RC2. Since there is a workaround, let's target this to 1.0.1.

I'll also add I'm not completely happy with the proposed fix. 
It appears to (still) be based on making sure the document has some content when open, instead of making sure the editor can tolerate empty content. 

Editors should be able to tolerate empty content, even though, I know, we also want to make it easy for a user to get started, often providing some templates to pick from, for example. 

So, hopefully by 101, we can come up with a better fix (or, I can better understand the rationale behind this one).

Hi David, we decided to add the nodes to make it easier for the user.  However, I agree that we should better handle blank files or files without the root node from an editor-wide perspective.  We'll address that in 1.0.1.
